Interface TracedMethod


  • public interface TracedMethod

      • addRollupMetricName

        void addRollupMetricName(java.lang.String... metricNameParts)
        Metric names added here will be reported as roll-up metrics. A rollup metric is an extra unscoped metric that is reported in addition to the normal metric recorded for a traced method. An example of how the agent uses a rollup metric is the Database/all metric. Database tracers record a metric for specific table operations, Database/users/select for example, but they also record a Database/all rollup metric which represents all database operations.
        Parameters:
        metricNameParts - The segments of the rollup metric name. These values will be concatenated together separated by a `/` char.
